b.font: Event Stream Processing and State Management

div.font: Depending on software design, this could look like many things, but the idea is always the same: observe events & change state.

div.div: Clicks, taps, pointer movement, keystrokes, voice commands, touch gestures, joystick play, your reflection in a camera, AT input or what-have-you can all trigger events over time while the application process is running.

div.div: Application state and how it's managed is entirely context dependent, but is generally defined as "operational memory". JS variables, fetched (or un-fetched) data from api, DOM properties, URL params, and local storage are common locations for state in FE web systems.
